{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed16530c-1360-44f3-97e0-32be093201a9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Properties, Units and Labels"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "71e95a26-bb34-42a9-ba38-264f0eb121b6",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import xplt\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(4873153)\n",
    "\n",
    "xplt.apply_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "43ba9ed3-993f-4a8d-8ed7-33d1681465ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Properties are what makes this library easy to use while still very flexible.\n",
    "\n",
    "A property is anything that we can \"get\" from a dataset, either as an attribute `data.xyz`, an index `data[\"xyz\"]` or even a column in a pandas dataframe.  \n",
    "For brevity, consider the following arbitrary dataset in the following:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "8492a417-24bd-432d-9910-50462f805ca5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# custom data\n",
    "N = 10000\n",
    "data = {\n",
    "    \"h\": np.linspace(0, 100, num=N),\n",
    "    \"w\": np.random.normal(size=N),\n",
    "    \"x\": np.random.normal(size=N),\n",
    "    \"y\": np.random.normal(size=N),\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed969bf7-02c6-41ca-b34a-34592426f31e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we can plot the x-y-phasespace simply by specifying exactly that:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "3fc57f50-2886-44b0-8481-5f592576f49a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(data, \"x-y\", display_units=dict(y=\"m\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ef8f5f0-a192-422e-8fb1-b3e1d590b013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This works, because both `x` and `y` are standard properties which are defined in the library with default settings for units, labels and symbols.\n",
    "Here specifically, the assumption is that `x` is provided in meters since that is the SI unit used by [Xsuite](https://xsuite.readthedocs.io), and that the default display unit for `x` should be millimeters. You can specify a display unit, and the data is automatically converted accordingly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "049f12e8-6fea-4702-b89d-09d46ec0fa52",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "See below for a list of predefined properties and the default assumed. You can add or change properties and their respective units, labels and symbols if required.\n",
    "Futher, derived properties can easily be defined building on the already existing ones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d8900a12-e203-4cb5-a0fe-8c73c1e59b11",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ddd540f-1425-4ef4-98e0-910cb9431e2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Adding custom data properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "18846981-e120-47df-bb71-ab071fc55918",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To define or overwrite properties of a data object with a certain units or meaning, you can either register them globally:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "ad08d5aa-934b-45cf-9198-fb2f6f411d0b",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# data[\"w\"] is the width in km\n",
    "xplt.register_data_property(\"w\", data_unit=\"km\", symbol=\"$w_x$\", description=\"Width\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c0a01ace-2986-4ac3-a292-5bd7d77e0f91",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Or on-the-fly for a single plot with the `data_units` parameter.\n",
    "Both enable automatic axes and legend labeling, as well as the use of the `display_units` parameter:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "5b350c6a-5c1a-4418-8389-e2e533ac84f5",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# data[\"h\"] is in mm\n",
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(data, \"w-h\", data_units={\"h\": \"mm\"}, display_units={\"h\": \"cm\"})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b57f78b9-61de-4e52-a7e9-77417adc4910",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a7178442-dc93-4e1c-a6d5-d7f7ffade16c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Derived properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "50389201-c814-42f9-a943-599798fd61cf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It is often useful to add properties that depend on already existing ones,\n",
    "e.g. if you simply want to plot the squareroot of a parameter, or have a complex expression.\n",
    "The function parameters must be valid property names, such that the data and units can be inferred automatically.\n",
    "It is also possible to specify the unit explicitly where necessary."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "d067d612-7440-45f0-ac1c-f87295405486",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "xplt.register_derived_property(\n",
    "    \"A\", lambda x, y: x * y\n",
    ")  # since both x and y are know properties (in units of meter), A is known to be in meter²\n",
    "xplt.register_derived_property(\n",
    "    \"B\", lambda A: A + 6, unit=\"m^2\"\n",
    ")  # since the unit of `6` can not be inferred, we declare B to be in meter² too"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "01861b6c-9865-4f21-855d-fe1b892527fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.PhaseSpacePlot(data, \"A-w\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "35850138-4161-4b35-9f7f-cb06de1124e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3d559a40-3019-4c25-90fa-93672aefcb27",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Default properties"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "158cf9f2-ee0f-41e9-85b0-9f1c0baf6d95",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A list of the default global properties:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "95970470-7c91-4d01-8b18-6b201dee5cdb",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-input"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Key              Unit      Symbol                Description\n",
      "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
      "alfx             1         $\\alpha_x$            \n",
      "alfy             1         $\\alpha_y$            \n",
      "at_turn          1         $n$                   Turn\n",
      "betx             m         $\\beta_x$             \n",
      "bety             m         $\\beta_y$             \n",
      "charge_ratio     1         $q/q_\\mathrm{ref}$    Charge ratio\n",
      "chi              1         $q/q_\\mathrm{ref} \\cdot m_\\mathrm{ref}/m$  Charge-over-rest-mass ratio\n",
      "count            1         $N$                   Count\n",
      "delta            1         $\\delta$              \n",
      "dpx              1         $D_{x'}$              \n",
      "dpy              1         $D_{y'}$              \n",
      "dx               m         $D_x$                 \n",
      "dy               m         $D_y$                 \n",
      "energy           eV        $E$                   Total energy\n",
      "gamx             1/m       $\\gamma_x$            \n",
      "gamy             1/m       $\\gamma_y$            \n",
      "m                eV/c^2    $m$                   Rest mass\n",
      "mass0            eV/c^2    $m_\\mathrm{ref}$      Reference rest mass\n",
      "mux              1         $\\mu_x$               \n",
      "muy              1         $\\mu_y$               \n",
      "ptau             1         $p_\\tau$              \n",
      "px               1         $x'$                  \n",
      "py               1         $y'$                  \n",
      "pzeta            1         $p_\\zeta$             \n",
      "q                e         $q$                   Charge\n",
      "q0               e         $q_\\mathrm{ref}$      Reference charge\n",
      "s                m         $s$                   \n",
      "tau              m         $\\tau$                \n",
      "x                m         $x$                   \n",
      "x_mean           m         $\\langle x \\rangle$   \n",
      "x_std            m         $\\sigma_x$            \n",
      "y                m         $y$                   \n",
      "y_mean           m         $\\langle y \\rangle$   \n",
      "y_std            m         $\\sigma_y$            \n",
      "zeta             m         $\\zeta$               \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"{'Key':15s}  {'Unit':8s}  {'Symbol':20s}  {'Description'}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 80)\n",
    "for name, prop in sorted(xplt.properties._default_properties.items()):\n",
    "    print(f\"{name:15s}  {prop.unit:8s}  {prop.symbol:20s}  {prop.description or ''}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a97bf84-f6c7-49a9-bec2-ac3a4e51e714",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "A list of properties available for particle data related plots (ParticlesPlot, PhaseSpacePlot, etc.):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "76548fc8-ebd5-4db6-9334-0d9e5317bef5",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-input"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Key              Unit      Symbol                Description\n",
      "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
      "Jx               m         $J_x$                 \n",
      "Jy               m         $J_y$                 \n",
      "Px               m^(1/2)   $X'$                  \n",
      "Py               m^(1/2)   $Y'$                  \n",
      "X                m^(1/2)   $X$                   \n",
      "Y                m^(1/2)   $Y$                   \n",
      "t                s         $t$                   \n",
      "zeta_wrapped     m         $\\zeta$               \n",
      "Θx               rad       $Θ_x$                 \n",
      "Θy               rad       $Θ_y$                 \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.particles.ParticlesPlot()\n",
    "print(f\"{'Key':15s}  {'Unit':8s}  {'Symbol':20s}  {'Description'}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 80)\n",
    "for p in sorted(plot._default_properties):\n",
    "    prop = plot.prop(p)\n",
    "    print(f\"{p:15s}  {prop.unit:8s}  {prop.symbol:20s}  {prop.description or ''}\")\n",
    "xplt.mpl.pyplot.close()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed09ebf8-f463-44af-a84a-bbf93e9a7e0e",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Futher properties are listed in the documentation of each plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "36e9d117-f62c-46a5-b5c4-c532339ca575",
